CNIBaseCloudRxProvider<T> - Class in com.conichi.sdk.dataprovider.rx.impl
CNIDataProvider implementation which provides caching mechanism that saves data in both persistent storage and memory(RAM).
Main difference between this and CNIBaseRxProvider is that BaseCloudDataProvider will automatically load the data from server if cache is empty.

In case if you need to obtain the data from specific source (server or local cache) - use CNIBaseCloudRxProvider.getEntity(DataSource): DataSource.CLOUD - to fetch the latest data from server and cache it DataSource.LOCAL - to obtain cached data

The common case is that your app received push notification and you know that data for specific data provider has been changed - in this case you have to call CNIBaseCloudRxProvider.getEntity(DataSource) with DataSource.CLOUD argument

CNIBaseCloudRxProvider(CNIStorage) - Constructor for class com.conichi.sdk.dataprovider.rx.impl.CNIBaseCloudRxProvider
 
CNIBaseRxProvider<T> - Class in com.conichi.sdk.dataprovider.rx.impl
CNIDataProvider implementation which provides caching mechanism that saves data in both persistent storage and memory(RAM).
To cache the data obtained from server call CNIBaseRxProvider.saveEntity(Object)
If you need to check if an entity is cached use CNIBaseRxProvider.isInLocalCache()
To obtain the latest saved data use CNIBaseRxProvider.getEntity().
